=head1 DESCRIPTION

Summary information about a target.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Id => Str

The ID of the target. If the target group type is C<INSTANCE>, this is
an instance ID. If the target group type is C<IP>, this is an IP
address. If the target group type is C<LAMBDA>, this is the ARN of a
Lambda function. If the target type is C<ALB>, this is the ARN of an
Application Load Balancer.


=head2 Port => Int

The port on which the target is listening.


=head2 ReasonCode => Str

The code for why the target status is what it is.


=head2 Status => Str

The status of the target.

=over

=item *

C<DRAINING>: The target is being deregistered. No new connections are
sent to this target while current connections are being drained. The
default draining time is 5 minutes.

=item *

C<UNAVAILABLE>: Health checks are unavailable for the target group.

=item *

C<HEALTHY>: The target is healthy.

=item *

C<UNHEALTHY>: The target is unhealthy.

=item *

C<INITIAL>: Initial health checks on the target are being performed.

=item *

C<UNUSED>: Target group is not used in a service.

=back




